article.headline: Colorado State 83, Texas State 65
article.story: FORT COLLINS, Colo. (AP) -- Matt Nelson had 18 points and nine rebounds to lead Colorado State to an 83-65 victory over Texas State Tuesday night. Matt Williams added 16 points as Colorado State (6-4) ended a two-game losing streak. The Rams were 22-for-28 from the free throw line. Josh Naylor scored 17 points on five 3-pointers, including one four minutes into the second half that pulled Texas State (5-3) to within 44-38. Nelson then scored eight of 10 points to give Colorado State a 52-42 lead with 14:40 left. Stephen Verwers and Dwight Boatner later scored with 3:45 remaining to extended Colorado State's lead to 74-54. Naylor kept Texas State within striking distance in the first half with three, 3-pointers. Naylor's teammates struggled against the taller Rams frontline and trailed 40-29 at halftime. Jason Smith scored 12 of his 14 points by the break, including two on a no look pass from Michael Morris in the last minute of the half. Anthony Dill had 16 points for Texas State which had its three-game winning streak snapped.
